/ Mother Jones Mass Shootings]\n* [https://www.gannett-cdn.com/GDContent/mass-killings/index.html USA Today Mass Shootings]\n* [https://www.vox.com/a/mass-shootings-america-sandy-hook-gun-violence Vox Mass Shootings]\n* [https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/national/mass-shootings-in-america/ Washington Post Mass Shootings]\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in the United States]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in the United States| ]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:2020-related lists|Mass shootings in the United States]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in the United States by year]]\n", "text_old": "<br />\n{{Main|List of mass shootings in the United States}}{{Map of 2020 United States mass shootings}}\nThis is a list of [[mass shootings in the United States]] that have occurred in 2020.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/10/04/the-squishy-definition-of-mass-shooting-complicates-media-coverage/|title=The squishy definition of 'mass shooting' complicates media coverage|last=Borchers|first=Callum|date=October 4, 2017|website=Washington Post|language=en|access-date=August 26, 2018|quote=...'mass shooting' is a term without a universally-accepted definition.}}</ref> This article only includes shootings with at least four total victims, including the shooter(s). <!--Update this figure MONTHLY only--> As of February 29, there have been 55 shootings that fit this criteria, resulting in 74 deaths and  199 injuries, for a total of 273 victims.<!--Update this figure MONTHLY only-->\n\n[[Gun Violence Archive]], a nonprofit research group that tracks shootings and their characteristics in the United States, defines a mass shooting as an incident in which four or more people, excluding the perpetrator(s), are shot in one location at roughly the same time.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.gunviolencearchive.org/methodology|title=General Methodology|last=|first=|date=|website=Gun Violence Archive|access-date=August 27, 2018}}</ref> The [[Congressional Research Service]] narrows that definition, limiting it to \"public mass shootings\", and defined by four or more victims killed. It excludes counting wounded survivors.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R43004|title=Public Mass Shootings in the United States|last=Bjelopera|first=Jerome|date=March 18, 2013|website=Congressional Research Service|access-date=December 6, 2019|quote=\"There is no broadly agreed-to, specific conceptualization of this issue, so this report uses its own definition for public mass shootings.\"}}</ref> ''[[The Washington Post]]'' and [[Mother Jones (magazine)|''Mother Jones'']] use similar definitions, with the latter acknowledging that their definition \"is a conservative measure of the problem\", as shootings with fewer fatalities occur.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/national/mass-shootings-in-america/|title=More than 50 years of U.S. mass shootings: The victims, sites, killers and weapons|last=Berkowitz|first=Bonnie|last2=Lu|first2=Denise|date=September 14, 2018|website=Washington Post|language=en|access-date=August 27, 2018|last3=Alcantara|first3=Chris}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2012/07/mass-shootings-map/|title=A Guide to Mass Shootings in America|last=Follman|first=Mark|date=September 20, 2018|work=Mother Jones|access-date=August 26, 2018|last2=Aronsen|first2=Gavin|language=en-US|last3=Pan|first3=Deanna}}</ref> The [[Crowdsourcing|crowdsourced]] Mass Shooting Tracker project defines a mass shooting as \"an incident where four or more people are shot in a single shooting spree. This may include the shooter themself, or police shootings of civilians around the shooter.\"<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910151639/https://www.massshootingtracker.org/about|archivedate=September 10, 2019|url=https://www.massshootingtracker.org/about|title=Mass Shooting Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=Mass Shooting Tracker|access-date=August 26, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Definitions ==\n[[Stanford University]] MSA Data Project: three or more persons shot in one incident, excluding the perpetrator(s), at one location, at roughly the same time. Excluded are shootings associated with organized crime, gangs or drug wars.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://library.stanford.edu/projects/mass-shootings-america|title=Mass Shootings in America|date=|website=Stanford Libraries|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=July 2, 2019|last3=Complaints|first3=California 94305 Copyright}}</ref>\n* Mass Shooting Tracker: four or more persons shot in one incident, at one location, at roughly the same time.<ref name=\":4\" />\n* [[Gun Violence Archive]]/''[[Vox (website)|Vox]]'': four or more shot in one incident, excluding the perpetrators, at one location, at roughly the same time.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Lopez |first=German |title=The debate over how to define mass shootings is ridiculous |url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2015/12/4/9850758/mass-shooting-definition |date=December 4, 2015 |work=[[Vox (magazine)|Vox]] |access-date=August 27, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Mother Jones (magazine)|''Mother Jones'']]: three or more shot and killed in one incident at a public place, excluding the perpetrators.<ref name=\":3\" />\n* ''[[The Washington Post]]'': four or more shot and killed in one incident at a public place, excluding the perpetrators.<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[ABC News]]/[[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]: four or more shot and killed in one incident, excluding the perpetrators, at one location, at roughly the same time.<ref name=ABC>{{cite news |last=Keneally |first=Meghan |title=There were 2 deadly mass shootings a month so far in 2019 |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/deadly-mass-shootings-month-2019/story?id=63449799 |date=June 5, 2019|website=[[ABC News]]|access-date=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Congressional Research Service]]: four or more shot and killed in one incident, excluding the perpetrators, at a public place, excluding gang-related killings and those done with a profit-motive.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOnly incidents considered mass shootings by at least two of the above sources are listed below.\n\n== List ==\n<!-- Please refrain from adding \" {{Expand list}}\". -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 8rem;\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 10rem;\" | Location\n! 0| Dead\n! 1| Injured\n! 1| Total\n! class=unsortable | Description\n<!-- Please add {{dts}} to every event. -->|-\n|{{Dts|March 31, 2020}}\n|[[Macon, Georgia]]\n|3\n|1\n|'''4'''\n|A domestic argument escalated when a man shot and killed his child's mother, step-father, and sister before abducting his 2-year-old child. The shooter was arrested and the child recovered after an [[Amber alert|Amber Alert]] was issued.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wgxa.tv/news/local/at-least-three-people-found-dead-inside-home-on-moreland-avenue|title=Deputies: Man wanted for murder, kidnapping after three found dead in Macon|last=Staff|first=WGXA Digital|date=2020-03-31|website=WGXA|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|March 30, 2020}}\n|[[Philadelphia|Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]\n|0\n|5\n|'''5'''\n|Five people were wounded at a late night memorial gathering, after a man fired into the crowd from half-a-block away. The wounded included a two-year-old, fourteen-year-old and an eighteen-year-old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2020/03/31/police-5-people-including-2-year-old-boy-shot-in-north-philadelphia-during-family-party-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=Police: 5 People, Including 2-Year-Old Boy, Shot In North Philadelphia During Family Party Amid Coronavirus Outbreak|last=|first=|date=2020-03-31|website=CBS 3 Staff|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-31}}</re