, tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://orf.at/stories/3156035/|title=Infektion in Steiermark: Bereits sieben best\u00e4tigte CoV-F\u00e4lle|last=red|first=ORF at/Agenturen|date=2020-02-28|website=news.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Belgium]]''' \u2013\nNine patients diagnosed with the virus had travelled from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.info-coronavirus.be/fr/2020/03/04/10-nouveaux-patients-contamines-par-le-covid-19-dans-notre-pays-sur-495-tests/|title=Coronavirus COVID-19|website=www.info-coronavirus.be|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Belgium has confirmed that there are many more and that Italy is the source of most of its cases.\n\n'''[[Belarus]]''' \u2013\nA case was confirmed as having been imported from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://belsat.eu/en/news/six-coronavirus-cases-in-belarus-ministry/|title=Six coronavirus cases in Belarus - ministry|website=belsat.eu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/03/04/belarus-coronavirus/1666615|title=Six coronavirus cases confirmed in Belarus - aysor.am - Hot news from Armenia|first=Helix Consulting|last=LLC|website=www.aysor.am|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]''' \u2013\nA man working in Italy transmitted the virus to his child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/03/05/bosnia-confirms-two-coronavirus-cases-expects-more/|title=Bosnia Confirms Two Coronavirus Cases, Expects More|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Bulgaria]]''' \u2013 On 8 March, Bulgaria confirmed its first two cases.\n\n'''[[Croatia]]''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Croatia confirmed its first case, a 26-year-old man who had stayed in Milan between 19 and 21 February and was hospitalised at the Dr. Fran Mihaljevi\u0107 University Hospital for Infectious Diseases in [[Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Newey|first=Sarah|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/science-and-disease/coronavirus-news-uk-italy-china-south-korea-pandemic/|title=Coronavirus latest news: Britons returning from Italy told to self-isolate as Matt Hancock says he is 'worried'|date=2020-02-25|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2020-02-25|last2=Kelly-Linden|first2=Jordan|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|last3=Team|first3=Global Health Security}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2160148|title=U Rijeci potvr\u0111en tre\u0107i slu\u010daj koronavirusa u Hrvatskoj|website=www.index.hr|language=hr|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\nOn 26 February, the man's twin brother tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital. A Croatian man who worked in [[Parma]], Italy also tested positive and was admitted to a hospital in [[Rijeka]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n'''[[Cyprus]]''' \u2013\nOne of the country's first two cases had a travel history to Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cyprus-mail.com/2020/03/10/hospital-close-to-shutdown-after-doctor-with-virus-treated-patients-update-5/|title=Hospital close to shutdown after doctor with virus treated patients (Update 5)|first=Peter|last=Michael|date=9 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Czech Republic]]''' \u2013\nOn 1 March, Czech Republic confirmed its first three cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/koronavirus-2019-ncov-aktualni-data_18455_4122_1.html|title=COVID-19: aktu\u00e1ln\u00ed data|website=DR|language=cs|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> As of 8 March 24 of 31 confirmed cases in the country have links to Italy, leading the government to institute a mandatory quarantine for all persons with a history of recent travel to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-nemocnice-bulovka-pocet-potvrzenych-pripadu.A200308_124539_domaci_remy|title=Koronavirus: 32 p\u0159\u00edpad\u016f, kontroly na hranic\u00edch i omezen\u00ed v domovech senior\u016f|date=8 March 2020|website=iDNES.cz|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Denmark]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Denmark confirmed its first case, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in [[Valmalenco]], [[Sondrio]] and was tested at [[Zealand University Hospital, Roskilde]] and quarantined at home.<ref name=Braagaard2020>{{cite news | last=Braagaard | first=Natali | date=27 February 2020 | title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus | url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus | publisher=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV2 News]] | language=Danish | trans-title=Dane infected with coronavirus | accessdate=27 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/foerste-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus-vi-er-selvfoelgelig-dybt-rystede|title=F\u00f8rste dansker smittet med coronavirus: 'Vi er selvf\u00f8lgelig dybt rystede'|website=DR|language=da-DK|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in Northern Italy on 15 February tested positive at [[Rigshospitalet]] in Copenhagen and was placed in home quarantine.<ref name=\"sst28February\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sst.dk/da/Nyheder/2020/En-person-der-er-blevet-undersoegt-paa-Rigshospitalet-er-det-andet-bekraeftede-tilfaelde-af-COVID-19|title=En person, der er blevet unders\u00f8gt p\u00e5 Rigshospitalet, er det andet bekr\u00e6ftede tilf\u00e6lde af COVID-19 i Danmark|date=28 February 2020|work=Sundhedsstyrelsen (Danish Health Authority)|language=da|trans-title=A person, that has been tested at Rigshospitalet, is the second confirmed case of COVID-19 in Denmark|url-status=live|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 29 February, an employee at the [[Aarhus University Hospital]] who had been to a conference in Munich, Germany, where he had met an infected person from Italy, tested positive.<ref name=Ingvorsen2020>{{cite news | last=Ingvorsen | first=Emil S\u00f8nderg\u00e5rd | date=29 February 2020 | title=Nyt coronatilf\u00e6lde er en medarbejder p\u00e5 Aarhus Universitetshospital | url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/nyt-coronatilfa