lth Commission}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Malaysia]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, Malaysia confirmed that a 54-year-old Italian who was married to a Malaysian tested positive and was admitted to [[Sungai Buloh Hospital]]. He was in Italy from 15 to 21 February for work.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/512562|title=After week-long lull, Malaysia records three new Covid-19 cases in 24 hours|date=2020-02-28|website=Malaysiakini|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Maldives]]''' \u2013\nThe Maldives' first cases were two staffers at Kuredu Island Resort who caught the disease from an Italian tourist who had returned to Italy and tested positive there.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/maldives-confirms-first-two-coronavirus-cases-two-resort-islands-locked-down/articleshow/74535526.cms|title=Maldives confirms first two coronavirus cases; two resort islands locked down|date=2020-03-08|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Oman]]''' \u2013\nA case was recorded of a patient who had travelled to Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofoman.com/article/2857238/Oman/Health/One-new-case-of-coronavirus-reported-in-Oman|title=One new case of coronavirus reported in Oman|date=5 March 2020|website=Times of Oman|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Philippines]]''' \u2013\nCase 441 had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Baguio City confirms first case of COVID-19 |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/23/baguio-city-first-covid-19-case.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Saudi Arabia]]''' \u2013\nOn 14 March, Saudi Arabia announced 17 new cases, including some citizens who had recently travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Saudi Arabia announces 17 new cases of coronavirus |url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1641471/saudi-arabia |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=Arab News |date=14 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Singapore]]''' \u2013\nCase 136 had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-cases-discharged-eight-more-cases-of-covid-19-infection-confirmed |title = MOH &#124; News Highlights}}</ref>\n\n'''[[South Korea]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, South Korea confirmed that a 38-year-old man living in [[Gwangjin District|Gwangjin]] who visited Milan from 19 to 24 February was admitted to Seoul Medical Centre.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20200228125600004 |script-title=ko:\uad11\uc9c4\uad6c\uc11c\ub3c4 \ud655\uc9c4\uc790\u2026\uc774\ud0c8\ub9ac\uc544 \ucd9c\uc7a5 \ud6c4 \ubc1c\ubcd1 | trans-title=Guangjin-gu is also confirmed\u2026 Onset after a business trip in Italy |last=\uc784\ud654\uc12d|date=2020-02-28|website=\uc5f0\ud569\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=023&aid=0003511260&sid1=001 |script-title=ko:\uc11c\uc6b8 \uad11\uc9c4\uad6c\uc11c \uccab \ud655\uc9c4\uc790 1\uba85 \ubc1c\uc0dd\u2026\uc774\ud0c8\ub9ac\uc544 \ubc00\ub77c\ub178 \ucd9c\uc7a5 \ub2e4\ub140\uc640|website=news.naver.com|language=ko|date=2020-02-28|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Sri Lanka]]''' \u2013\nLike nearby Maldives, Sri Lanka was also affected by a group of infected Italian tourists, who passed on the disease to a 52-year-old tour guide upon their visit to the island nation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adaderana.lk/news/61290/first-sri-lankan-coronavirus-patient-in-the-country-identified |title=First Sri Lankan coronavirus patient in the country identified |publisher=Adaderana.lk |date=2019-10-23 |accessdate=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Thailand]]''' \u2013\nOn 5 March, Thailand announced that its 44th and 45th confirmed cases, a 29-year-old Italian and 42-year-old Thai, had arrived in Thailand from Italy on 2 March. Both were admitted in [[Chonburi Province]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pr.moph.go.th/?url=pr/detail/2/04/139480 |script-title=th:\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e02\u0e48\u0e32\u0e27\u0e01\u0e23\u0e13\u0e35\u0e44\u0e27\u0e23\u0e31\u0e2a\u0e42\u0e04\u0e42\u0e23\u0e19\u0e32 2019 (COVID-19) \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e08\u0e33\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 5 \u0e21\u0e35\u0e19\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21 2563|trans-title=Report of COVID-19 situation in Thailand, 5 March 2020|language=Thai|via=[[Ministry of Public Health (Thailand)|Ministry of Public Health, Thailand]]|date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[United Arab Emirates]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, two Italian staff members of the [[UAE Tour]], a cycling event, tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cyclists await test results after coronavirus hits UAE Tour |url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/sports/1868344/cyclists-await-test-results-after-coronavirus-hits-uae-tour |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Bangkok Post |date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Vietnam]]''' \u2013\nCase 17 had travelled to Italy (as well as to France and the UK).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lepetitjournal.com/ho-chi-minh/actualites/covid-19-au-vietnam-un-17eme-cas-confirme-hanoi-275441|title=COVID-19 au Vietnam : un 17\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Hanoi|website=lepetitjournal.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Europe===\n\n'''[[Albania]]''' \u2013\nOn 9 March, a 54-year-old man and his 28-year-old son, who had travelled from Florence to Albania by car, were confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Konfirmohen dy rastet e para me koronavirusin e ri |url=http://shendetesia.gov.al/ministria-e-shendetesise-konfirmohen-dy-rastet-e-para-me-koronavirusin-e-ri/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |date=9 March 2020 |language=Albanian}}</ref> Three other people from the men's family were suspected of having the virus. Another Albanian who had gone to Italy for a one-day trip is suspected.\n\n'''[[Andorra]]''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Andorra registered its first case, a 20-year-old man who had been to Milan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Andorra registra su primer caso de coro