rs|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a couple who tested positive and their two children who were showing symptoms were admitted to Kaiser-Franz-Josef Hospital. The family was previously on holiday in Lombardy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wien.orf.at/stories/3036506/|title=Coronavirus: Drei best\u00e4tigte F\u00e4lle in Wien|last=red|first=wien ORF at/Agenturen|date=2020-02-27|website=wien.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derstandard.at/jetzt/livebericht/2000115088241/coronaviruserster-bestaetigter-fall-in-wien|title=Dritter best\u00e4tigter Coronavirus-Fall in Wien - derStandard.at|website=DER STANDARD|language=de-AT|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> On 28 February, one of the children, a 15-year-old boy, tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://orf.at/stories/3156035/|title=Infektion in Steiermark: Bereits sieben best\u00e4tigte CoV-F\u00e4lle|last=red|first=ORF at/Agenturen|date=2020-02-28|website=news.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Belgium]]''' \u2013\nNine patients diagnosed with the virus had travelled from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.info-coronavirus.be/fr/2020/03/04/10-nouveaux-patients-contamines-par-le-covid-19-dans-notre-pays-sur-495-tests/|title=Coronavirus COVID-19|website=www.info-coronavirus.be|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Belgium has confirmed that there are many more and that Italy is the source of most of its cases.\n\n'''[[Belarus]]''' \u2013\nA case was confirmed as having been imported from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://belsat.eu/en/news/six-coronavirus-cases-in-belarus-ministry/|title=Six coronavirus cases in Belarus - ministry|website=belsat.eu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/03/04/belarus-coronavirus/1666615|title=Six coronavirus cases confirmed in Belarus - aysor.am - Hot news from Armenia|first=Helix Consulting|last=LLC|website=www.aysor.am|accessdate=8 March 2020}